      <!-- Section 7: Implementation Steps -->
      <section id="implementation" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Implementation: A Conversational Search Optimisation Workflow</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>A practical conversational search optimisation workflow runs across five stages, from intent mapping through to measurement — and each stage builds directly on the last.</strong>
          Skipping the intent mapping stage and jumping to content creation is the most common mistake: it produces content that answers an isolated query well but misses the surrounding intent chain entirely.
        </p>

        <ol class="mt-6 space-y-6 list-none pl-0">
          <li class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent-600/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--accent)] font-mono font-bold text-sm">1</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Map the intent chain</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Identify the entry-point query and the two to four most probable follow-up questions. Use AI platforms directly — ask them questions in your target topic and observe the follow-up suggestions they generate. This is more reliable than keyword research tools, which are not designed for conversational query modelling.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent-600/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--accent)] font-mono font-bold text-sm">2</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Audit existing content for answer density</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Review your existing pages against the intent chain. Identify which stages are covered, which are missing, and which have answers buried in prose that should be surfaced as explicit, structured content units. Score each page on how many self-contained citable answers it contains per 500 words.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent-600/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--accent)] font-mono font-bold text-sm">3</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Restructure and expand content</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Rewrite each section to open with a bold declarative statement. Add a structured FAQ section with four to six Q&A pairs covering the intent chain stages. Add FAQPage schema matching the visible Q&A. Expand thin sections that address high-probability follow-up questions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent-600/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--accent)] font-mono font-bold text-sm">4</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Strengthen internal linking across the intent chain</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Ensure every page in your intent chain cluster links to adjacent pages in the chain. An AI system retrieving your page for stage two of a conversation is more likely to also retrieve your stage three page if it is explicitly linked and contextually related. Cross-links also reinforce topical authority signals.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent-600/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[var(--accent)] font-mono font-bold text-sm">5</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Measure AI citation coverage</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">Test each stage of the intent chain across Perplexity, ChatGPT, and Google AI Overviews. Record which queries cite your domain and which cite competitors. This gap analysis defines the next content sprint. Repeat quarterly, as AI platform retrieval behaviour shifts with model and index updates.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p class="mt-8">
          For help implementing this workflow across your content estate, including intent chain mapping and AI citation auditing, <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">contact GEOoptimised</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
      <div class="prose-dark mt-4">
        <h2 id="faq" class="anchor-top">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-2" id="faq-accordion">
        {faqs.map(faq => (
          <div class="card overflow-hidden" data-faq>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="flex w-full items-center justify-between p-5 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-white/[.02]"
              aria-expanded="false"
              data-faq-trigger
            >
              <span>{faq.q}</span>
              <span class="faq-icon ml-4 shrink-0 text-[var(--accent)] transition-transform duration-200" data-faq-icon>+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out" data-faq-panel>
              <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">{faq.a}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Related Reading -->
      <div class="mt-16">
        <span class="eyebrow" id="related">Related reading</span>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          {related.map(item => (
            <a href={item.href} class="card card-hover block p-5 no-underline">
              <span class="eyebrow">{item.tag}</span>
              <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-300">{item.excerpt}</p>
              <span class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[var(--accent)]">Read article <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

